# Copy to `.env.local` (gitignored) to point local dev at your **production** Postgres.
#
# Option A — pull all Production env vars from Vercel (needs `npm run vercel:link` once; use Node 22 — see README):
#   npm run env:pull:prod
#
# Option B — paste only the URL from Vercel → Project → Settings → Environment Variables → Production
#
# DATABASE_URL="postgresql://USER:PASSWORD@HOST/DB?sslmode=require"
#
# ⚠️ With a live DATABASE_URL, avoid `npm run db:push` / `db:migrate` unless you intend to change production schema.
